definition.value: Organ part cluster, which consists of some members of two or more organ subdivision subclasses which are grouped together according to some shared attributes. Examples: root of lung, neurovascular bundle, renal pedicle, fascia of back.
Organ component of the liver, which consists of irregular dense connective tissue sheath which surrounds each portal triad.
